WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:23.000 --> 00:25.230
<i><font color="#D900D9">(DAY IN THE SUN</i> PLAYING)</font>

00:36.680 --> 00:37.908
Want to grab that?

00:38.760 --> 00:40.432
I can't believe it's so crowded.

00:40.560 --> 00:42.391
School isn't even out yet.

00:42.520 --> 00:43.748
Maybe we should come back.

00:43.880 --> 00:45.757
How about never? That sound good?

00:46.040 --> 00:49.430
A family swim
is a great way to kick off the summer.

00:49.800 --> 00:52.473
Let's not forget, opening day is free!

00:52.960 --> 00:55.076
<i><font color="#D900D9">(DAY IN THE SUN</i> CONTINUES PLAYING)</font>

00:59.160 --> 01:00.388
I hate going in there.

01:00.680 --> 01:03.114
Remember, move fast
and keep your eyes down.

01:04.200 --> 01:05.349
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:06.920 --> 01:09.115
Sorry. Excuse me.

01:25.640 --> 01:26.629
<font color="#D900D9">(CRACKING)</font>

01:26.920 --> 01:27.989
Greg!

01:29.160 --> 01:32.709
I'm going to see if I can get a good spot.
Watch Manny.

01:33.240 --> 01:34.229
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> What? But... <font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:36.040 --> 01:37.109
Manny?

01:38.280 --> 01:39.349
Manny?

01:44.040 --> 01:45.109
Manny!

01:45.760 --> 01:47.193
<font color="#D900D9">(WATER RUNNING)</font>

01:55.040 --> 01:57.713
<font color="#D900D9">(CALLING OUT FOR MANNY)</font>

02:02.760 --> 02:03.988
Manny, no!

02:04.360 --> 02:06.396
Washing my hands.

02:09.960 --> 02:12.190
<i><font color="#D900D9">(ANOTHER SUNNY DAY</i> PLAYING)</font>

02:34.760 --> 02:35.829
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> No, no, no.

02:36.520 --> 02:38.715
But I'm so close to getting...

02:39.000 --> 02:42.959
Summertime is for
real games, not video games. Healthy stuff.

02:43.240 --> 02:45.913
Like, let's see...

02:46.040 --> 02:47.029
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLES)</font>

02:47.160 --> 02:48.388
Swimming?

02:50.720 --> 02:52.472
<i><font color="#D900D9">(ANOTHER SUNNY DAY
CONTINUES</i> PLAYING)</font>

03:15.320 --> 03:17.595
Time to sell some C.D.'s.

03:17.720 --> 03:18.948
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING LOUDLY)</font>

03:22.200 --> 03:23.428
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING)</font> Are you kidding?

03:23.800 --> 03:24.789
<font color="#D900D9">(TURNS MUSIC OFF)</font>

03:24.920 --> 03:27.434
Rodrick, you can't play
your music that loud.

03:27.720 --> 03:28.789
Lenwood?

03:29.400 --> 03:30.389
Is that Lenwood Heath?

03:30.680 --> 03:32.557
Mr. Heffley, it's good to see you.

03:34.520 --> 03:35.509
Mrs. Heffley.

03:36.200 --> 03:37.189
Hi.

03:37.720 --> 03:39.438
So... you've changed.

03:39.720 --> 03:42.234
I've been going to Spag Union Prep School.

03:42.600 --> 03:43.555
They really turned me around.

03:43.680 --> 03:46.319
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font> You may remember
I was a bit of a troublemaker.

03:46.920 --> 03:47.989
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> Nah.

03:51.560 --> 03:53.073
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING LOUDLY)</font>

03:55.640 --> 03:58.074
You're cleaning all this up! You hear me?

04:00.040 --> 04:01.109
<font color="#D900D9">(WHOOPING)</font>

04:04.200 --> 04:06.873
So, Spag Union, what grade does that start?

04:07.240 --> 04:08.229
Eighth grade, sir.

04:09.320 --> 04:10.275
Hey.

04:11.080 --> 04:12.718
You're going into the eighth grade.

04:14.600 --> 04:15.999
<font color="#808080">BOY:</font> Cannonball!

04:16.360 --> 04:18.714
It's good to see you, sir. Ma'am.

04:18.839 --> 04:19.909
<font color="#D900D9">(BLOWS WHISTLE)</font>

04:20.040 --> 04:21.439
He called me "sir".

04:22.280 --> 04:25.431
He used to be so cool. Like me.

04:25.720 --> 04:26.675
<font color="#D900D9">(SQUEAKS)</font>

04:29.960 --> 04:31.188
Löded Diper.

04:31.480 --> 04:32.879
<font color="#808080">MANNY:</font> Bubby, over here!

04:33.160 --> 04:35.037
Greg, honey, go help your brother.

04:41.040 --> 04:42.234
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

04:45.000 --> 04:45.989
What's so funny?

04:46.360 --> 04:47.759
I'm peeing!

04:55.080 --> 04:56.115
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

05:07.160 --> 05:08.479
Ugh, ugh!

05:08.600 --> 05:10.272
<i><font color="#D900D9">(DIARY OF A WIMPY KID</i> THEME PLAYING)</font>

05:10.400 --> 05:11.594
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

05:14.560 --> 05:15.549
<font color="#D900D9">(YELPS)</font>

05:22.000 --> 05:22.989
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

05:25.160 --> 05:26.752
<font color="#D900D9">(COINS CLINKING)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMS)</font>

05:33.840 --> 05:34.875
<font color="#D900D9">(DOG BARKING)</font>

05:35.000 --> 05:37.514
I have one more week
of school, then it's summer vacation.

05:37.760 --> 05:39.876
Which sounds great, but for me,

05:40.000 --> 05:42.468
summer vacation is basically
a three-month guilt trip.

05:42.720 --> 05:43.869
Just because the weather's nice,

05:44.000 --> 05:46.833
everyone expects you
to be out all day frolicking.

05:46.960 --> 05:48.359
<font color="#D900D9">(SINGING)</font> <i>La, la, la, la, la</i>

05:48.920 --> 05:52.071
But the truth is,
I've always been more of an indoor person.

05:52.320 --> 05:55.073
To me,
the perfect way to spend summer vacation

05:55.200 --> 05:57.077
is in front of the TV playing video games.

05:57.720 --> 05:59.756
<i>Unfortunately, my dad's idea of a perfect</i>

05:59.920 --> 06:01.990
<i>summer is the opposite of mine.</i>

06:02.240 --> 06:05.869
<i>The real problem is,
me and my dad have nothing in common.</i>

06:06.200 --> 06:08.919
<i>But as long as I stay one
step ahead of him...</i>

06:10.840 --> 06:12.876
...I think I have a shot at a fun summer.

06:14.440 --> 06:16.112
<i><font color="#D900D9">(ROCK 'N'ROLL HIGH SCHOOL</i> PLAYING)</font>

06:19.520 --> 06:20.873
Last day of school!

06:21.120 --> 06:23.156
I know. It's kind of sad.

06:23.520 --> 06:25.556
Sad? Are you crazy?

06:25.720 --> 06:28.280
I'm going to play video games all summer.
It's going to be awesome.

06:29.120 --> 06:30.519
There's one person I will miss.

06:31.320 --> 06:32.275
Hey, guys!

06:32.480 --> 06:33.674
<font color="#808080">BOTH:</font> Hi, Holly!

06:34.560 --> 06:36.278
You'll see her when school starts again.

06:36.600 --> 06:39.797
In three months?
A lot can happen in three months.

06:40.480 --> 06:42.152
Hey, Holly. How was your summer?

06:42.400 --> 06:43.913
Great! I got married.

06:45.240 --> 06:47.435
You know my husband... Chirag.

06:47.680 --> 06:48.715
Hello, Gregory.

06:50.680 --> 06:52.113
Last period of the school year!

06:52.480 --> 06:53.959
<font color="#D900D9">(STUDENTS WHOOPING)</font>

06:54.080 --> 06:56.719
But it is still a school day, so...

06:56.960 --> 06:59.190
...open <i>Discovering History</i> to chapter 7.

06:59.520 --> 07:02.830
It's the last day of school.
Like anyone brought their books.

07:05.400 --> 07:06.833
Classic Greg Heffley.

07:07.040 --> 07:07.995
I pity him.

07:08.320 --> 07:10.151
Of course you're not prepared.

07:10.400 --> 07:14.996
Mr. Draybick, I'd be honored to share my
book with Greg Heffley.

07:20.560 --> 07:22.835
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i> Fregley claims to
wear a special cologne,</i>

07:23.040 --> 07:25.315
<i>but everyone knows he just never washes.</i>

07:28.800 --> 07:30.279
That's great!

07:45.200 --> 07:46.189
<font color="#D900D9">(GIGGLING)</font>

07:48.800 --> 07:49.869
Rowley.

07:50.880 --> 07:53.394
I need to make a connection
with Holly this summer.

07:53.760 --> 07:55.318
I'm tired of being...

07:56.120 --> 07:57.109
..."friends".

07:57.760 --> 08:00.911
What's wrong with being "friends"?
We're friends.

08:02.200 --> 08:03.918
I'll get her to sign my yearbook.

08:04.440 --> 08:05.998
She signs lots of yearbooks.

08:06.240 --> 08:07.798
But when she signs mine, I'll ask her

08:08.000 --> 08:09.558
to write her phone number, too.

08:09.880 --> 08:10.835
<font color="#808080">MR. DRAYBICK:</font> Okay!

08:11.480 --> 08:13.038
The rest of the class is free time.

08:13.280 --> 08:14.508
<font color="#D900D9">(STUDENTS CHEERING)</font>
-<font color="#808080"> MR. DRAYBICK:</font> Enjoy.

08:22.080 --> 08:25.231
Hey, Holly.
What are you doing this summer?

08:25.560 --> 08:27.118
Just regular summer stuff.

08:27.360 --> 08:30.796
Volunteering at the shelter, building
with Habitat for Humanity...

08:31.040 --> 08:33.395
...and giving tennis
lessons to little kids.

08:33.919 --> 08:34.909
What about you?

08:35.320 --> 08:37.993
He's going to get to
the end of <i>Twisted Wizard 2</i> this summer!

08:40.440 --> 08:43.750
If I have time because
of all the other stuff I'm doing.

08:44.640 --> 08:46.995
Hey, can I sign your yearbook?

08:48.120 --> 08:50.839
Yeah, sure.
You're only in seventh grade once.

08:51.200 --> 08:52.189
<i>That's not always true, by the way.</i>

08:52.320 --> 08:55.949
<i>I think Andy Spitz
has been in seventh grade for four years.</i>

08:56.080 --> 08:57.149
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

08:57.920 --> 09:02.038
And... why don't
you write down your phone number, too?

09:02.360 --> 09:03.315
<font color="#D900D9">(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)</font>
- Okay.

09:03.440 --> 09:05.112
<font color="#D900D9">(STUDENTS CHEERING)</font>
- Let's go!

09:06.080 --> 09:07.308
Bye!

09:15.840 --> 09:17.068
No!

09:18.720 --> 09:19.994
<font color="#D900D9">(STUDENTS CHEERING)</font>

09:37.440 --> 09:38.475
<font color="#808080">CHIRAG:</font> Gregory!

09:39.040 --> 09:41.395
Help me! Help me!

09:45.120 --> 09:47.076
<font color="#D900D9">(STUDENTS CONTINUE CHEERING)</font>

09:57.240 --> 09:58.673
Would you sign my yearbook?

09:59.000 --> 10:00.069
Of course!

10:04.960 --> 10:06.837
Holly, you didn't finish writing...

10:07.160 --> 10:08.878
Isn't that your brother?

10:09.120 --> 10:12.430
<font color="#808080">RODRICK:</font> Löded Diper's
coming to rock a town near you!

10:13.600 --> 10:17.388
Aw! You're getting your yearbooks signed?
That is so cute.

10:19.200 --> 10:20.235
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

10:24.120 --> 10:25.109
What the heck?

10:27.040 --> 10:28.837
<font color="#808080">SUSAN:</font> Honey,
Greg was sick on picture day.

10:28.960 --> 10:30.996
Did you send in
a photo of him for the yearbook?

10:31.320 --> 10:33.356
Yeah! I remembered!

10:38.280 --> 10:39.554
<font color="#D900D9">(HORN HONKING)</font>

10:39.680 --> 10:40.829
<font color="#D900D9">(POP MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)</font>

10:40.960 --> 10:42.359
That's Heather Hills.

10:43.040 --> 10:44.029
Get in.

10:44.160 --> 10:45.718
But I need to finish
signing Greg's yearbook.

10:46.240 --> 10:47.593
News flash. I don't care.

10:48.800 --> 10:50.028
Sorry.

10:50.520 --> 10:51.589
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> But you didn't...

10:52.000 --> 10:53.558
So... Heather.

10:54.200 --> 10:56.555
I'm going on a world tour with my band.

10:56.960 --> 10:59.952
If you're around,
I could comp you chicks some tickets.

11:00.240 --> 11:01.229
Let's go.

11:01.360 --> 11:02.315
Wait! Holly!

11:02.480 --> 11:03.469
Ahh!

11:04.560 --> 11:06.039
Ow! Ow!

11:07.320 --> 11:10.630
She was trying to act cool,
but I know she was into me.

11:11.200 --> 11:13.031
"Rowley, you are so cute."

11:13.160 --> 11:14.513
Cute's underlined three times!

11:14.840 --> 11:19.277
"Stay cool. XOXO, Holly."
What did she write in yours?

11:21.440 --> 11:25.069
"Have a great summer.
You're such a good... friend."

11:25.320 --> 11:26.389
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

11:27.040 --> 11:28.075
"Friend"?

11:28.960 --> 11:30.678
Oh, man!

11:31.520 --> 11:34.478
That's the kiss of death. "Friend".
That sucks!

11:35.160 --> 11:36.991
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Despite Rodrick's negative attitude,</i>

11:37.160 --> 11:38.991
<i>I have very clear goals for the summer.</i>

11:39.360 --> 11:42.352
<i>One, play video games.
Two, get together with Holly.</i>

11:42.720 --> 11:44.597
<i>Or three, both at the same time.</i>

11:44.920 --> 11:46.638
Greg, you're an amazing gamer.

11:46.880 --> 11:48.233
I know.

11:48.600 --> 11:52.229
<i>Our neighbors, the Warrens, have
kids that are the outdoorsy type.</i>

11:52.480 --> 11:53.708
<i>That's okay, but...</i>

11:54.040 --> 11:55.268
<i>...my dad has this crazy idea</i>

11:55.400 --> 11:57.231
<i>that physical exercise is normal.</i>

11:57.560 --> 11:59.949
<i>Those guys are setting a bad example.</i>

12:01.400 --> 12:04.756
<i>My dad has his eye on me,
so the key to a successful summer...</i>

12:05.080 --> 12:07.116
<i>... will be to stay one move ahead.</i>

12:08.760 --> 12:11.638
Those Warren boys
are already up, raring to go.

12:12.000 --> 12:14.833
Our boys probably
won't even get up till noon.

12:15.480 --> 12:17.994
I'm sorry. Did you say something?

12:19.320 --> 12:20.389
What are you doing up?

12:20.960 --> 12:22.791
It's the first day of vacation.

12:22.960 --> 12:24.757
Did you think I'd just lie around all day?

12:25.120 --> 12:28.271
Actually, that's exactly what I thought.

12:28.600 --> 12:29.828
I can't find Manny's Tingy.

12:31.360 --> 12:33.715
You know, it's probably time...

12:34.040 --> 12:37.191
...for him to move on
from that ratty old blanket anyway.

12:37.440 --> 12:39.510
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i> Manny was given Tingy
right after he was born.</i>

12:39.680 --> 12:41.875
<i>Back then, Tingy was a fluffy blue blanket.</i>

12:42.240 --> 12:44.231
<i>But now, it's a couple of pieces of yarn</i>

12:44.400 --> 12:46.356
<i>held together with raisins and boogers.</i>

12:46.680 --> 12:48.398
You don't think he cares anymore?

12:48.680 --> 12:49.635
<font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERING)</font>

12:49.760 --> 12:51.955
I'm sure it'll turn up.

12:53.880 --> 12:54.869
What?

12:55.200 --> 12:56.758
Look at this garbage.

12:57.080 --> 12:59.594
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>My dad and I
don't agree on anything, except for...</i>

12:59.840 --> 13:01.273
<i>...the comic</i> Li'l Cutie.

13:01.400 --> 13:03.630
<i>We both hate it.
But we can't stop reading it!</i>

13:04.000 --> 13:07.788
You're my BFF... Best Father Forever!

13:08.160 --> 13:09.718
- It's not even a joke!
- I know.

13:10.040 --> 13:13.430
Can we please focus?
We need to find Manny's Tingy.

13:13.560 --> 13:14.595
<font color="#D900D9">(EXHALES)</font> Ohh!

13:14.720 --> 13:16.438
I'm going to be late for work.

13:17.440 --> 13:18.668
See you!

13:30.240 --> 13:31.798
Vacation is on!

13:32.480 --> 13:33.913
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

13:54.920 --> 13:55.955
Greg.

13:57.800 --> 13:58.994
Greg.

14:01.440 --> 14:04.750
Are you really going
to sit inside all day and play video games?

14:11.640 --> 14:12.629
<font color="#D900D9">(HISSING)</font>

14:26.800 --> 14:28.279
<font color="#D900D9">(TICKING)</font>

14:29.560 --> 14:30.675
<font color="#D900D9">(RINGING)</font>

14:44.080 --> 14:45.274
<font color="#D900D9">(BOYS GRUNTING)</font>

14:56.000 --> 14:57.035
- Hey.
- Oh.

14:57.160 --> 14:58.149
Hey, Dad.

14:58.360 --> 14:59.918
Are you... sweating?

15:00.360 --> 15:04.148
Yeah, I just finished up
some sports... playing.

15:04.400 --> 15:05.469
Uh-huh.

15:06.120 --> 15:07.348
How was your day?

15:07.640 --> 15:10.632
Horrible! Manny
still hasn't recovered from losing Tingy.

15:11.160 --> 15:15.278
Well, maybe it's for the best.
I think he should really move on.

15:15.880 --> 15:17.108
Tingy!

15:18.120 --> 15:21.112
Tingy! Oh, my gosh, honey,
you found your blanket!

15:21.480 --> 15:23.835
This is great, but how
did it end up in the...

15:24.160 --> 15:25.115
Garbage?

15:25.240 --> 15:26.229
Frank?

15:26.720 --> 15:27.709
Yeah?

15:27.920 --> 15:28.955
You didn't.

15:29.240 --> 15:30.309
I didn't...

15:30.920 --> 15:31.989
...know...

15:32.680 --> 15:36.309
...that it meant that much to him anymore.

15:37.560 --> 15:38.549
How could you?

15:42.920 --> 15:43.989
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMS IN SURPRISE)</font>

15:44.120 --> 15:45.678
- Good morning<font color="#808080">.
 RODRICK:</font> - Morning!

15:49.280 --> 15:52.352
<i>Congratulations, player,
all your hard work has paid off.</i>

15:52.720 --> 15:55.393
<i>You're now a Level Nine Necromancer!</i>

15:56.880 --> 15:58.836
You played video games all day.

15:59.120 --> 16:00.189
Me? <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)</font>

16:01.200 --> 16:04.033
No. I've been playing sports.

16:04.720 --> 16:08.349
That's it! No more
video games for the rest of the summer!

16:08.880 --> 16:09.869
You can't do that!

16:10.080 --> 16:12.594
Oh, yeah, I can! I will! I am!

16:12.880 --> 16:14.916
I'm unplugging it!

16:15.200 --> 16:17.634
Does the DVD or the cable box go into...

16:17.920 --> 16:20.195
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>
- Does the DVD player go into the cable...

16:20.480 --> 16:22.118
You think this is funny?

16:22.400 --> 16:23.799
It's amusing.

16:25.040 --> 16:27.713
Well, then how about no video games and...

16:28.000 --> 16:31.629
...no television for the rest of the summer?
Does that make you laugh?

16:31.760 --> 16:32.749
Dad, no!

16:32.960 --> 16:34.518
I stopped laughing!

16:38.040 --> 16:38.995
Ha!

16:39.120 --> 16:42.590
Guess who's the laugher now? Me!
I'm the laugher!

16:42.880 --> 16:45.440
I'm the laugh ingest laugher
that ever laughed!

16:45.560 --> 16:48.518
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

16:50.000 --> 16:51.228
Funny stuff!

16:53.200 --> 16:55.395
I'm going to work on my battle diorama.

16:55.680 --> 16:56.669
Frank!

16:57.520 --> 17:00.751
What are you doing?
First Tingy, and now Greg's video games?

17:01.040 --> 17:02.837
General Lee isn't going to paint himself.

17:04.240 --> 17:05.388
This is important.

17:05.520 --> 17:08.990
You can't take away everything they love
and disappear downstairs.

17:09.359 --> 17:12.113
You need to get
to Greg's level and really engage with him.

17:12.960 --> 17:15.155
Find an activity you both enjoy.

17:16.400 --> 17:19.790
What are we going to do,
play <i>Twisted WarlockalL</i> day?

17:20.079 --> 17:23.231
I hate to say it,
but we have absolutely nothing in common.

17:23.599 --> 17:25.556
What Greg needs is a role model.

17:25.839 --> 17:29.150
Someone he can look up to.
Sit down and talk with him.

17:29.440 --> 17:31.556
I do, but he doesn't listen to me.

17:31.840 --> 17:34.991
Trust me, hanging out
together is no fun for either of us.

17:37.040 --> 17:38.359
You always complain that your father

17:38.480 --> 17:39.708
never spent enough time with you

17:39.840 --> 17:41.068
when you were young.

17:42.800 --> 17:44.836
Now you're doing the same thing.

17:47.120 --> 17:49.634
Be the father you wish
your father had been.

17:54.080 --> 17:55.308
You're right.

17:58.640 --> 18:00.517
I should put in more time.

18:01.840 --> 18:03.717
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>That didn't sound good.</i>

18:05.520 --> 18:07.875
Rise and shine!

18:08.400 --> 18:09.958
It's Saturday!

18:10.480 --> 18:12.516
We get to spend the whole day together!

18:19.200 --> 18:20.428
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> You know...

18:21.360 --> 18:22.759
...it takes a while to get here

18:22.880 --> 18:24.199
and it's an effort to get the boat out...

18:25.040 --> 18:26.439
...but this is what it's all about.

18:26.720 --> 18:29.075
You and me, spending
quality time together.

18:30.960 --> 18:32.916
Okay, buddy, hand me some bait.

18:38.000 --> 18:38.989
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMS IN SURPRISE)</font>

18:46.800 --> 18:47.869
Well...

18:49.120 --> 18:50.997
...we should think about getting back.

18:55.760 --> 18:57.318
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>As bad as this was...</i>

18:57.600 --> 19:01.070
<i>...Mom 's idea of
a good summer activity was even worse.</i>

19:01.360 --> 19:02.759
I'm so glad...

19:03.040 --> 19:05.076
...you all decided
to become founding members

19:05.200 --> 19:07.236
of the Reading Is Fun Club!

19:07.760 --> 19:08.749
So...

19:09.040 --> 19:10.678
...let's share the books you brought.

19:16.320 --> 19:18.675
I'm not so sure these
qualify as literature.

19:18.960 --> 19:21.793
How about I get some real books? Classics.

19:22.480 --> 19:24.038
Something to stimulate your minds.

19:25.440 --> 19:26.919
I'll be right back!

19:28.400 --> 19:32.109
Thank you so much, Gregory,
for making the summer a time...

19:32.320 --> 19:33.878
...to study and write book reports.

19:34.240 --> 19:37.391
You think I want to do this?
My summer's turned into a nightmare.

19:37.600 --> 19:39.158
You should come with me
to the country club!

19:39.320 --> 19:42.357
It's really fun
and you get to be outside all day.

19:44.560 --> 19:46.118
Ta-da!

19:48.240 --> 19:50.196
Let's get this party started! Oh, yeah!

19:50.520 --> 19:51.999
Mmm-hmm.

19:52.960 --> 19:56.350
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>What do I do? I want to call Holly,
but the number's no good.</i>

19:56.640 --> 19:58.358
<font color="#808080">ROWLEY:</font> Only the last
two numbers are missing.

19:58.640 --> 20:01.950
That means there's only
100 different numbers it could be.

20:02.160 --> 20:03.388
I've got it!

20:03.840 --> 20:07.230
I'll call every number
it could be until I get the right one.

20:12.880 --> 20:14.916
Hello? Freggers speaking.

20:19.840 --> 20:21.239
Hello? Pickup or delivery?

20:21.760 --> 20:22.749
This is Brad.

20:22.880 --> 20:23.869
Hello?

20:26.720 --> 20:27.948
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

20:31.840 --> 20:33.068
This is the coach.

20:33.360 --> 20:34.918
<font color="#808080">BOTH:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERING)</font> Coach Malone?

20:35.200 --> 20:36.189
Who is this?

20:36.400 --> 20:37.879
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERING)</font> Don't tell him, Greg.

20:38.160 --> 20:39.718
Greg? Greg who?

20:40.160 --> 20:42.833
Okay, listen up, "Greg".
I don't know who you are...

20:43.120 --> 20:45.236
...but if you call again,
I'll reach through the phone...

20:46.320 --> 20:49.710
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>So far, this is
shaping up to be the worst summer ever.</i>

20:50.360 --> 20:51.793
<font color="#D900D9">(PLAYING BUGLE BADLY)</font>

20:53.280 --> 20:54.315
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

20:56.320 --> 20:59.153
Come on!
We'll be late for the Battle of Phillipi!

21:01.120 --> 21:02.189
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

21:03.760 --> 21:06.513
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Dad's really into Civil
War reenactments, which are basically...</i>

21:06.800 --> 21:08.836
<i>...a bunch of grown men dressed</i>

21:09.000 --> 21:11.070
<i>as soldiers running around in muddy fields.</i>

21:11.360 --> 21:14.830
<i>I didn't get to carry a gun.
I had the honor of being bugle boy.</i>

21:15.120 --> 21:19.557
We re-enactors pride ourselves
on being completely authentic.

21:20.000 --> 21:21.069
Ronnie...

21:21.680 --> 21:23.875
...carved his own buttons
out of black rubber.

21:24.720 --> 21:29.316
And Artie... his underwear,
made out of horsehair.

21:30.880 --> 21:32.279
<font color="#D900D9">(VIDEO GAME SOUNDS)</font>

21:32.400 --> 21:33.799
What are you doing?

21:34.480 --> 21:36.357
It's spring, 1861!

21:36.720 --> 21:38.995
We're trying to outflank
Porterfield's armies!

21:39.160 --> 21:41.469
There's no video games! Come on!

21:42.640 --> 21:43.629
Okay, okay.

21:43.800 --> 21:46.439
All right. Now, the deciding factor...

21:46.800 --> 21:49.075
...the reason we win this battle...

21:49.240 --> 21:51.549
is we hold the element of surprise.

21:53.240 --> 21:54.958
<font color="#D900D9">(PLAYING BADLY)</font>

21:55.080 --> 21:56.115
No!

21:56.240 --> 21:58.754
No, we need the element of surprise!

21:59.120 --> 22:00.269
That kid ruined everything!

22:00.440 --> 22:01.634
<font color="#808080">CONFEDERATE SOLDIER:</font> Let's get him!

22:02.360 --> 22:03.509
<font color="#D900D9">(GUNFIRE)</font>

22:04.280 --> 22:05.838
Where are you going?

22:06.320 --> 22:08.072
It's a reenactment! We won!

22:26.960 --> 22:27.915
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

22:28.840 --> 22:30.558
<font color="#D900D9">(RINGING)</font>

22:31.640 --> 22:32.629
Hello?

22:32.760 --> 22:35.115
Hey, Greg. I can't make
it to the book club.

22:35.440 --> 22:38.113
My mom's taking me to the country club.
She said I could invite you.

22:38.360 --> 22:39.588
No, thanks.

22:39.920 --> 22:43.071
Let's crack open <i>Little Women</i> and
see what's up with the girls.

22:45.360 --> 22:46.759
I'll be right over!

22:50.840 --> 22:52.398
We're going to have so much fun!

22:52.720 --> 22:53.948
If you say so.

22:55.720 --> 22:56.675
<font color="#808080">LENWOOD:</font> Up!

22:57.040 --> 22:58.598
Up! Up!

23:03.280 --> 23:05.157
Up! Come on!

23:05.680 --> 23:07.557
Davey, you call that a push-up?

23:21.200 --> 23:22.189
Hello, Mrs. Jefferson.

23:22.360 --> 23:23.395
<font color="#808080">MRS. JEFFERSON:</font> Hi, Amy.

23:23.920 --> 23:24.875
Crowded today?

23:25.200 --> 23:27.111
The nice weather really brought people out.

23:30.000 --> 23:32.673
Wow! Amy wasn't kidding!

23:33.040 --> 23:34.917
It is crowded today.

23:38.480 --> 23:40.198
This is crowded?

23:45.200 --> 23:46.918
Care for a smoothie?

23:47.280 --> 23:48.508
They bring stuff to you?

23:48.680 --> 23:49.954
Yes, they do.

23:50.520 --> 23:51.953
<i><font color="#D900D9">(THE GOOD LIFE</i> PLAYING)</font>

23:54.600 --> 23:55.635
Yes!

23:59.320 --> 24:00.548
Sorry!

24:00.880 --> 24:03.075
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i> I guess I do like being outside...</i>

24:03.600 --> 24:05.477
<i>...when I'm outside at a country club.</i>

24:07.320 --> 24:08.309
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> It's Holly Hills!

24:08.440 --> 24:09.429
She's always here.

24:09.680 --> 24:10.908
She's a member.

24:12.120 --> 24:14.759
And you didn't think maybe
you should tell me that?

24:15.640 --> 24:18.598
Now it's step... swing... catch it up high.

24:19.720 --> 24:20.789
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

24:21.520 --> 24:24.353
Bye! And remember, work on your forehand.

24:26.280 --> 24:27.269
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> Hey, Holly.

24:27.400 --> 24:28.355
Hey, guys!

24:28.720 --> 24:30.836
I thought you were going to call me.

24:31.120 --> 24:34.271
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font> I was going to,
but... then I realized I'd see you here.

24:34.560 --> 24:36.118
So, what are you up to?

24:36.400 --> 24:37.753
I'm helping the tennis coach.

24:37.880 --> 24:39.871
I give lessons to little kids.

24:40.720 --> 24:42.836
That's so weird. We're all about tennis!

24:43.520 --> 24:45.476
Cool! We should play sometime.

24:45.760 --> 24:47.637
Actually, I've never played...

24:47.920 --> 24:49.319
We'd love to play!

24:50.000 --> 24:51.479
What about tomorrow at eleven?

24:51.760 --> 24:53.318
Eleven's perfect.

24:53.680 --> 24:54.829
See you tomorrow!

24:55.000 --> 24:56.194
Tomorrow it is!

24:57.840 --> 25:00.115
And that's how you improve your summer.

25:01.480 --> 25:02.959
<font color="#808080">BOTH:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(SINGING)</font> <i>La, la, la, la</i>

25:03.320 --> 25:04.799
<i>La, la, la, la, la, la</i>

25:05.040 --> 25:06.109
<font color="#808080">SUSAN:</font> <i>No, no.</i>

25:06.480 --> 25:09.472
More. More. Oh, come on, Manny!

25:09.760 --> 25:10.829
Hi, Mom.

25:10.960 --> 25:13.633
Wow. Somebody looks like
they actually had fun.

25:13.760 --> 25:14.749
Hello!

25:15.040 --> 25:16.029
Hello.

25:16.480 --> 25:17.435
Just the guy I'm looking for.

25:17.560 --> 25:18.595
Me?

25:18.720 --> 25:21.871
My office is offering a summer internship.

25:22.160 --> 25:23.718
And I signed you up for it!

25:24.080 --> 25:25.229
What's an internship?

25:25.400 --> 25:26.594
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> Well...

25:26.880 --> 25:29.553
You'll come to my office every day...

25:29.840 --> 25:32.991
...but you'll have your own responsibilities.
It's like a job.

25:33.280 --> 25:34.838
- Do I get paid?
- No.

25:35.120 --> 25:36.838
You got me a non-paying job?

25:37.200 --> 25:39.077
You can be work buddies!

25:44.320 --> 25:45.389
How long till we go home?

25:46.160 --> 25:48.116
We got here eight minutes ago!

25:52.880 --> 25:54.916
It sounds really great, but...

25:56.240 --> 25:58.117
This is awkward.

25:58.400 --> 26:00.595
It's just that... I already got a job.

26:00.880 --> 26:02.438
What? You got a job?

26:02.720 --> 26:05.075
Yeah! Rowley invited me
to the country club...

26:05.360 --> 26:07.715
...and I saw a "Help Wanted" sign.

26:08.000 --> 26:10.355
I went to the manager and he hired me.

26:11.120 --> 26:13.156
He said he liked my pluck.

26:14.000 --> 26:15.069
Wait.

26:15.440 --> 26:17.158
You actually got a job?

26:17.520 --> 26:20.990
Yeah. But I can call and tell
him I can't if you want me...

26:21.280 --> 26:24.670
No, no! That's fantastic!
Can you believe it, Susan?

26:25.360 --> 26:26.588
Our son got himself a job!

26:26.760 --> 26:28.034
I know.

26:31.520 --> 26:34.512
Somebody around here
actually did something.

26:37.520 --> 26:38.919
It's great!

26:42.640 --> 26:43.675
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

26:44.400 --> 26:46.231
<font color="#D900D9">(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

26:50.600 --> 26:53.558
<i>Keeping you down
The new sheriff in town</i>

26:53.680 --> 26:56.478
<i>I'm the man
I'm the man, I'm the man</i>

26:57.040 --> 27:00.635
<i>Don't mess with me, hoss
'Cause I lay down the laws</i>

27:00.760 --> 27:03.399
<i>I'm the man
I'm the man, I'm the man</i>

27:05.040 --> 27:08.191
I think we should tell her
we've never played tennis.

27:08.560 --> 27:11.313
We played <i>Ultimate Tennis</i>
on the Wii, it's the same thing.

27:12.320 --> 27:13.355
Hi, guys.

27:13.520 --> 27:14.509
<font color="#808080">BOTH:</font> Hi, Holly!

27:14.800 --> 27:15.869
Jinx!

27:21.760 --> 27:24.115
Oh, no. What is she doing here?

27:24.800 --> 27:25.949
Should we start with a rally?

27:26.120 --> 27:27.269
What's that?

27:27.640 --> 27:30.279
Oh, Rowley. Can you ever be serious?

27:30.680 --> 27:31.999
They'll let anyone in this place.

27:32.440 --> 27:33.668
That must be why you're here.

27:34.040 --> 27:34.995
Hey!

27:35.120 --> 27:38.112
Let's play doubles.
Patty and me versus you two.

27:38.360 --> 27:39.395
Okay.

27:41.360 --> 27:42.315
I'm gonna kill you!

27:50.960 --> 27:51.915
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS LOUDLY)</font>

27:52.920 --> 27:53.875
Hey!

27:54.000 --> 27:55.228
Sorry.

27:55.920 --> 27:57.478
Fifteen, love.

27:59.640 --> 28:00.629
What'd she call me?

28:01.240 --> 28:02.992
<font color="#808080"><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>
 GREG:</font> - Ow!

28:03.120 --> 28:04.109
<font color="#808080">PATTY:</font> Yes!

28:04.720 --> 28:05.994
I mean, oops.

28:06.800 --> 28:08.358
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>
- Thirty, love.

28:08.720 --> 28:10.915
Whatever you say... love!

28:11.760 --> 28:12.829
What?

28:13.400 --> 28:14.913
He's a weirdo.

28:15.520 --> 28:16.589
<i><font color="#D900D9">(CELEBRATE SUMMER</i> PLAYING)</font>

28:16.720 --> 28:19.029
<i>Hey, little girl,
would you like a dance?</i>

28:19.160 --> 28:20.275
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font> Yes!

28:20.400 --> 28:22.231
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

28:22.360 --> 28:25.636
<i>Hey, little girl,
want a quick romance?</i>

28:25.760 --> 28:29.548
<i>Hey, little girl,
won't you take a chance</i>

28:30.040 --> 28:33.669
<i>And celebrate summer with me</i>

28:34.840 --> 28:38.389
<i>Hey, little chick,
where'd you learn that trick?</i>

28:39.400 --> 28:42.949
<i>Hey, don't you know
you got rock and roll?</i>

28:43.760 --> 28:47.469
<i>Hey, little girl,
won't you take a chance</i>

28:48.080 --> 28:49.911
I got it! I got it!

28:50.040 --> 28:51.712
<i>And celebrate summer with me</i>

28:53.720 --> 28:54.709
Oh!

28:58.160 --> 29:01.470
Have either of you
actually played tennis before?

29:01.840 --> 29:04.070
Yeah... <i>Ultimate Tennis</i> on the Wii.

29:05.680 --> 29:07.398
It's not exactly the same thing.

29:08.400 --> 29:09.992
I could give you a few pointers.

29:15.440 --> 29:18.113
You have to follow through. Like this.

29:23.200 --> 29:24.155
Ugh!

29:24.280 --> 29:25.349
We have to go. It's an emergency.

29:25.560 --> 29:26.629
A mega-emergency.

29:26.960 --> 29:29.952
The printer messed
up the invitations for my Sweet Sixteen.

29:30.200 --> 29:32.077
What does that have to do with me?

29:33.080 --> 29:36.550
People have expectations.
Everything has to be perfect!

29:37.400 --> 29:40.039
You'll never understand
what it's like to be pretty.

29:41.360 --> 29:42.918
Can you drive me home later?

29:43.160 --> 29:45.515
Come back for you? No.
It's like ten minutes away!

29:45.640 --> 29:47.278
Now move it or lose it.

29:50.160 --> 29:51.229
Wow!

29:51.600 --> 29:52.828
I know, right?

29:53.680 --> 29:55.238
I'll see you guys later!

29:57.240 --> 29:58.150
Bye!

29:58.840 --> 30:01.195
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Not bad for
the first day of my fake job.</i>

30:01.520 --> 30:04.034
<i>Plus, now Dad and I
are both "working men "...</i>

30:04.600 --> 30:05.828
<i>... we get along great.</i>

30:06.040 --> 30:07.712
Happy Fourth of July!

30:10.200 --> 30:13.670
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> "<i>Li'l Cutie</i> cartoonist
to retire in three months"!

30:14.040 --> 30:15.758
We won't have to read
that garbage anymore!

30:15.920 --> 30:17.797
Good riddance!

30:18.160 --> 30:19.195
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Every Fourth of July,</i>

30:19.320 --> 30:22.596
<i>our neighbors, the Warrens,
throw a big party for the whole block.</i>

30:22.960 --> 30:25.793
<i>Mom and Dad make us all go. Which is bad...</i>

30:26.160 --> 30:29.152
<i>...because I've been
a voiding Rodrick's built-in lie detector.</i>

30:29.400 --> 30:30.355
Hey, worker bee.

30:30.640 --> 30:33.950
You know, you having a job
doesn't pass the smell test.

30:34.320 --> 30:35.912
Yes, it does. It totally does!

30:40.240 --> 30:41.195
Here, sweetie.

30:41.320 --> 30:42.275
Thanks.

30:46.320 --> 30:48.993
With my boys, it's go, go, go!

30:49.120 --> 30:51.076
I have to wrestle them in every night.

30:51.600 --> 30:53.158
Same with my boys.

30:53.440 --> 30:56.591
They're in my Wilderness
Explorers troop now. They love it!

30:56.880 --> 30:59.553
I loved being in the Wilderness Explorers.

31:00.160 --> 31:01.798
- You did?
- Yeah. Loved it.

31:02.080 --> 31:05.629
That one camping trip
we took as kids, you cried the whole time.

31:06.480 --> 31:09.313
Well, I broke my arm in two places.

31:10.400 --> 31:11.389
Cried the whole time.

31:11.680 --> 31:12.635
Yeah, I...

31:13.360 --> 31:14.429
It hurt.

31:14.800 --> 31:18.110
You know what?
You should join the Wilderness Explorers.

31:18.720 --> 31:20.358
I'm more of an indoor person.

31:20.640 --> 31:21.868
Exactly. When's the next meeting?

31:22.160 --> 31:24.071
The waiting list for our
troop is a mile long.

31:24.200 --> 31:26.236
Everybody wants to join
the best of the best.

31:26.360 --> 31:27.634
<font color="#D900D9">(BARKING)</font>

31:27.760 --> 31:30.274
Is that your dog? We grew up with a dog.

31:30.640 --> 31:32.517
Nutty. Frank named him.

31:32.800 --> 31:34.995
You can never be too young
to learn responsibility.

31:35.120 --> 31:36.678
You should get your boys a dog.

31:37.680 --> 31:39.557
Yeah. That's a great idea.

31:44.000 --> 31:46.753
I think I'll speak to Dad
about my suspicions.

31:47.440 --> 31:48.759
Do whatever you want.

31:50.480 --> 31:51.708
I will.

31:54.480 --> 31:55.708
Okay! Okay!

31:57.760 --> 31:59.478
I don't really have a job.

31:59.840 --> 32:00.875
Holly Hills is a member,

32:01.000 --> 32:02.991
if I'm at the country club,
I can hang out with her.

32:03.200 --> 32:04.428
I knew it.

32:04.560 --> 32:06.073
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

32:06.800 --> 32:08.119
So is Heather Hills there, too?

32:09.200 --> 32:10.758
- Heather who?
- I want in.

32:11.600 --> 32:13.875
I can't get you in there.
I go as Rowley's guest.

32:14.160 --> 32:15.639
I'll go as your guest.

32:15.920 --> 32:17.831
I can't bring the guest. I am the guest.

32:17.960 --> 32:19.313
There's no guest for the guest.

32:19.440 --> 32:20.429
Mmm...

32:20.560 --> 32:21.629
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

32:21.760 --> 32:23.830
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Things are getting complicated.</i>

32:23.960 --> 32:25.791
<i>But at least something good
came out of the barbecue.</i>

32:26.080 --> 32:27.069
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> Introducing...

32:27.760 --> 32:30.274
...the new member of the Heffley family!

32:30.840 --> 32:32.910
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMS)</font>
- Hey, hey!

32:33.040 --> 32:34.598
Oh, Frank.

32:34.880 --> 32:36.598
I wish you'd checked with me first.

32:37.200 --> 32:39.634
I think this is more of a family decision.

32:40.320 --> 32:41.389
Who's a good puppy?

32:41.520 --> 32:42.509
We can call him Shredder!

32:42.800 --> 32:43.755
No.

32:43.880 --> 32:44.835
Rip jaw?

32:45.200 --> 32:47.077
We can call him Sweetie.

32:47.600 --> 32:48.555
<font color="#808080">SUSAN:</font> Sweetie!

32:48.960 --> 32:50.518
Sweetie, that's a great name!

32:50.800 --> 32:52.028
Yeah. Yeah.

32:52.720 --> 32:54.836
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Dad was willing to go
with any name Mom wanted</i>

32:54.960 --> 32:57.076
<i>if it meant
he didn't have to take the dog back.</i>

32:57.400 --> 32:58.992
<i><font color="#D900D9">(I'M THINKING SUNSHINE</i> PLAYING)</font>

33:01.360 --> 33:02.588
Sweetie!

33:03.360 --> 33:04.349
Sweetie.

33:04.640 --> 33:05.834
<font color="#D900D9">(BARKING)</font>
- Oh!

33:08.960 --> 33:10.154
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMS IN DISGUST)</font>

33:13.360 --> 33:14.918
Sweetie! Sweetie!

33:15.160 --> 33:16.195
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

33:26.080 --> 33:28.275
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>I always thought
I wanted a dog, but...</i>

33:28.560 --> 33:30.437
<i>...I'm having second thoughts.</i>

33:31.280 --> 33:33.475
All right, ready? Sit. Sit!

33:33.840 --> 33:35.956
Good! Hey, did you see that?

33:36.240 --> 33:37.434
Okay, now shake.

33:37.560 --> 33:38.834
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLES)</font> Yoo-hoo!

33:38.960 --> 33:40.996
Shake. Shake.

33:41.360 --> 33:42.509
Here you go.

33:44.720 --> 33:46.119
"Sweaty"?

33:47.520 --> 33:49.795
I'm pretty sure it spells Sweetie, Dad.
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

33:50.200 --> 33:51.269
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

33:53.360 --> 33:54.588
Wow.

33:58.960 --> 34:01.793
I love you.

34:09.760 --> 34:10.987
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>With Sweetie around, I'd hoped</i>

34:11.159 --> 34:13.833
<i>Dad would forget
about joining the Wilderness Explorers.</i>

34:14.199 --> 34:16.873
<i>But Dad connected
with his old troop master.</i>

34:18.199 --> 34:20.077
As your father knows...

34:20.400 --> 34:23.755
...we take our scouting
very seriously in Troop 133.

34:24.080 --> 34:25.034
It's true.

34:25.239 --> 34:28.072
Only the very best
get to be part of this troop.

34:28.280 --> 34:30.635
It's so great to
be back here, Troop Master Barrett!

34:30.960 --> 34:32.951
Now, you boys get yourselves a uniform,

34:33.120 --> 34:35.110
and the first thing you'll do...

34:35.639 --> 34:39.268
...is clean out that musty
old storage locker.

34:39.639 --> 34:41.197
Oh! <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

34:41.560 --> 34:43.277
Oh, really? Okay.

34:44.600 --> 34:46.591
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Dad got more than he bargained for.</i>

34:46.840 --> 34:49.991
<i>But he couldn't wiggle out of
it, that would set a bad example.</i>

34:50.320 --> 34:52.993
<font color="#808080">BARRETT:</font> Whittling is
the kind of skill you'll need...

34:53.239 --> 34:56.197
...for our upcoming wilderness weekend.

34:59.800 --> 35:01.313
I'm getting splinters.

35:01.560 --> 35:02.788
This is impossible.

35:05.200 --> 35:07.555
I have finished, Troop Master Barrett!

35:09.880 --> 35:12.713
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>It seems the only break I'll get
this summer is at the country club.</i>

35:13.360 --> 35:16.079
<i>That is, as long as Rodrick
doesn't ruin things.</i>

35:16.560 --> 35:17.913
<font color="#808080">RODRICK:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERING)</font> Hey!

35:19.760 --> 35:21.637
Don't forget about me.

35:22.520 --> 35:24.238
Go around the back!

35:30.040 --> 35:31.268
Marco!

35:32.120 --> 35:33.189
Polo!

35:34.360 --> 35:35.588
Marco!

35:36.280 --> 35:37.474
Polo!

35:38.440 --> 35:40.874
<font color="#D900D9">(BOYS CONTINUE PLAYING MARCO POLO)</font>

35:55.960 --> 35:57.188
Rodrick?

35:57.880 --> 35:58.949
Rodrick!

35:59.280 --> 36:01.840
<font color="#D900D9">(IN BRITISH ACCENT)</font> Hello, guvnor!
Top of the crumpet to you! Ooh!

36:02.640 --> 36:06.599
Where's the nearest loo, mate?
Mustered up a wee little tinkle!

36:06.840 --> 36:08.239
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>I don't want to sound like a snob,</i>

36:08.400 --> 36:10.960
<i>but I'm not sure Rodrick
is country club material.</i>

36:11.320 --> 36:12.548
<font color="#808080">ROWLEY:</font> Marco!

36:12.880 --> 36:13.949
Polo!

36:14.200 --> 36:16.839
Wow! You can hold your breath
a really long time!

36:17.080 --> 36:18.638
Would you like another smoothie?

36:18.960 --> 36:19.949
No, thanks. Polo!

36:20.120 --> 36:21.519
I'd like to order a few things.

36:21.880 --> 36:22.949
He's not serious.

36:23.280 --> 36:26.909
I'm very serious. Two orders of
fries, vanilla shake extra thick...

36:27.160 --> 36:28.513
...and anything with bacon on it.

36:29.400 --> 36:30.799
Fish out of water!

36:31.160 --> 36:34.311
Finally! I thought I'd never find you!

36:35.000 --> 36:36.228
What's Rodrick doing here?

36:36.760 --> 36:39.274
I got invited! You got a problem?

36:39.640 --> 36:41.312
No! No problem!

36:43.160 --> 36:46.152
Mom is going to kill you!
When did you get a tattoo?

36:46.480 --> 36:48.675
There's a lot you
don't know about me, Greggy.

36:49.400 --> 36:52.358
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Having Rodrick
at the country club really made me nervous.</i>

36:53.560 --> 36:55.869
<i>I told him to keep a low profile.</i>

36:56.040 --> 36:58.315
<i>I didn't want to get
fired from my fake job.</i>

36:58.680 --> 37:01.353
<i>But, of course, he didn't listen.</i>

37:07.800 --> 37:09.358
It's Heather Hills time.

37:10.000 --> 37:11.274
Don't go over there.

37:11.640 --> 37:14.154
I'm not. She's coming to me.

37:15.640 --> 37:17.312
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Rodrick did have a plan.</i>

37:17.720 --> 37:20.553
<i>Unfortunately, he came up with it himself.</i>

37:21.080 --> 37:24.390
<i>I guess he saw Heather's Lifeguard
outfit and figured she'd be into...</i>

37:24.720 --> 37:26.312
<i>...saving people and stuff.</i>

37:30.040 --> 37:31.029
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

37:31.160 --> 37:32.149
Cramp!

37:32.280 --> 37:35.431
Excuse me.
What time does the snack bar close?

37:35.800 --> 37:38.792
What am I, a guidebook?
Come back when you're drowning.

37:39.120 --> 37:40.109
Cramp!

37:41.520 --> 37:42.919
There's no need to be mean.

37:43.160 --> 37:45.515
Help! Hey, look, I'm drowning! Hey!

37:46.520 --> 37:49.239
Listen, shrimp, the reason I'm
here in this ridiculous outfit

37:49.400 --> 37:50.913
is to get credit for my
college application.

37:52.120 --> 37:53.519
Oh! I can't...

37:54.360 --> 37:55.429
I'm drowning!

37:57.080 --> 37:58.638
So bounce.

37:59.800 --> 38:01.995
Cramp! Help! Help!

38:02.680 --> 38:03.999
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font> What the...

38:04.200 --> 38:05.155
I got you!

38:05.360 --> 38:06.315
<font color="#808080">RODRICK:</font> Who are you?

38:06.640 --> 38:08.039
- I don't even know you!
- You're okay.

38:08.280 --> 38:09.998
What is happening?

38:11.800 --> 38:12.789
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

38:14.840 --> 38:15.795
<font color="#D900D9">(COUGHS)</font>

38:17.480 --> 38:18.629
Ohh!

38:24.240 --> 38:25.593
<font color="#D900D9">(SOBBING)</font>

38:33.880 --> 38:35.518
Guess what?

38:35.640 --> 38:36.868
We're going to the shore this weekend

38:37.080 --> 38:38.308
and my mom said I could invite you!

38:38.640 --> 38:40.471
The boardwalk's awesome.

38:40.600 --> 38:43.068
Go on the Cranium Shaker.
You haven't lived till you've done that.

38:43.320 --> 38:44.548
You should come!

38:44.880 --> 38:48.031
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i> I think most people would agree
I'm a pretty likeable kid...</i>

38:48.280 --> 38:51.590
<i>...but for some reason,
I've never clicked with Mr. Jefferson.</i>

38:56.120 --> 38:57.678
<font color="#808080">SUSAN:</font> Greg. Honey.

38:59.640 --> 39:01.995
Your father and I
have something to give you.

39:02.320 --> 39:06.108
You've showed us
you're responsible enough to have one.

39:06.640 --> 39:07.868
Your own cell phone.

39:08.120 --> 39:10.156
Are you serious? My own cell phone?

39:15.760 --> 39:17.318
It doesn't have a keypad.

39:17.680 --> 39:20.513
It's a starter phone.
You can call home or 911.

39:20.760 --> 39:22.318
We didn't want to overwhelm you.

39:23.960 --> 39:25.188
Thanks.

39:28.560 --> 39:29.834
Have a good time!

39:32.280 --> 39:33.349
See you.

39:39.440 --> 39:40.998
We're going to the boardwalk!

39:41.160 --> 39:42.752
I can't wait to ride the Cranium Shaker!

39:43.000 --> 39:45.195
The Cranium Shaker?

39:46.040 --> 39:47.393
You're too funny, Greg.

39:48.040 --> 39:49.189
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

39:50.000 --> 39:51.274
<font color="#808080">MRS. JEFFERSON:</font> Who wants to sing?

39:51.640 --> 39:52.629
Me!

39:53.240 --> 39:55.549
<font color="#808080">ALL:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(SINGING)</font> <i>Five thousand bottles
of milk on the wall</i>

39:55.680 --> 39:57.352
<i>Five thousand bottles of milk</i>

39:57.720 --> 39:59.756
<i>Take one down, pass it around</i>

40:00.080 --> 40:03.072
<i>Four thousand nine hundred ninety-nine
Bottles of milk on the wall</i>

40:10.160 --> 40:13.311
<i>Sixteen bottles of milk on the wall
Sixteen bottles of milk</i>

40:13.560 --> 40:17.678
<i>Take one down, pass it around
Fifteen bottles of milk on the wall</i>

40:27.760 --> 40:29.478
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>We're so far from the boardwalk.</i>

40:30.240 --> 40:33.391
Oh, yeah! It's much quieter up here!

40:36.160 --> 40:39.789
<font color="#808080">MRS. JEFFERSON:</font> <i>Why don't
we play "I love you because "?</i>

40:39.920 --> 40:40.909
<font color="#808080">ROWLEY:</font> <i>Yay!</i>

40:41.040 --> 40:42.268
I'll start.

40:47.280 --> 40:48.508
I love you because...

40:49.120 --> 40:51.554
...you're silly and you make me laugh.

40:53.680 --> 40:54.829
My turn.

41:00.800 --> 41:02.358
I love you because...

41:03.680 --> 41:05.796
...you help me keep my body clean!

41:08.160 --> 41:09.388
<font color="#808080">ROWLEY:</font> Your turn, Greg.

41:14.800 --> 41:16.677
Land on me, land on me!

41:26.240 --> 41:28.117
I love you because...

41:29.920 --> 41:32.593
...your mustache is... really...

41:36.800 --> 41:38.836
...because...

41:42.080 --> 41:43.479
...because...

41:46.560 --> 41:48.118
...because...

41:49.520 --> 41:51.556
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i> How do you even win this game?</i>

41:54.040 --> 41:55.678
<i><font color="#D900D9">(LA LA LA</i> PLAYING)</font>

42:05.680 --> 42:07.159
It's awfully crowded here.

42:07.440 --> 42:09.396
It's quieter at the amusement park.

42:09.680 --> 42:11.238
Who wants ice cream?

42:11.520 --> 42:13.078
- Yay! Strawberry!
- Vanilla for me.

42:13.360 --> 42:15.476
Rocky Road! Thanks.

42:31.120 --> 42:33.395
We like to share, it's more fun that way.

42:35.600 --> 42:36.589
Would you like some?

42:37.360 --> 42:38.588
Oh, no, thanks.

42:39.040 --> 42:41.713
I just remembered I'm lactose intolerant.

42:43.360 --> 42:46.193
Meet us back here in exactly one hour.

42:46.560 --> 42:48.596
And no scary rides for you boys.

42:48.880 --> 42:49.869
Got it.

42:53.920 --> 42:55.797
Cranium Shaker, here we come.

42:56.160 --> 42:57.878
<font color="#808080">ROWLEY:</font> But my mom said...

42:58.200 --> 43:00.236
<i><font color="#D900D9">(GOOD FEELING</i> PLAYING)</font>

43:07.520 --> 43:09.238
We'll come back later
when the line goes down.

43:46.040 --> 43:47.268
<font color="#D900D9">(WOLF HOWLING)</font>

43:47.960 --> 43:49.109
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING EVILLY)</font>

43:51.680 --> 43:52.749
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMING IN DISTRESS)</font>

43:56.320 --> 43:57.799
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> There's no line!

44:02.000 --> 44:05.151
I did promise my mom
we wouldn't go on any scary rides.

44:05.440 --> 44:07.192
But Rodrick says you haven't lived till

44:07.320 --> 44:09.072
you've been on the Cranium Shaker.

44:09.360 --> 44:10.349
Have you been on this ride?

44:10.480 --> 44:11.469
It's way scary.

44:11.600 --> 44:13.158
Did you hear what happened last summer?

44:13.760 --> 44:15.034
My brother knows a guy

44:15.160 --> 44:16.593
whose second cousin's half-brother

44:16.760 --> 44:18.193
went on this ride and got decapitated.

44:18.480 --> 44:19.469
<font color="#808080">GIRL 2:</font> No way!<font color="#808080">
GIRL 1:</font> Way.

44:19.600 --> 44:22.114
It's true. I was working the ride that day.

44:23.520 --> 44:27.638
The car came down
and his head... wasn't in it.

44:32.640 --> 44:35.313
When you guys get to the top...

44:35.840 --> 44:38.673
...be sure not to rock
the car back and forth.

44:39.040 --> 44:40.268
That's how...

44:46.920 --> 44:48.478
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE SCREAMING)</font>

44:52.120 --> 44:53.189
<font color="#D900D9">(BEEPING)</font>

44:53.840 --> 44:54.989
<font color="#D900D9">(BELL RINGING)</font>

45:07.520 --> 45:08.999
<font color="#D900D9">(CREAKING)</font>

45:09.360 --> 45:11.237
He said not to rock the car!

45:11.520 --> 45:13.238
Or our heads will be torn off!

45:15.360 --> 45:18.238
Greg, in case we don't make it,

45:18.360 --> 45:19.839
there's something I have to tell you.

45:20.320 --> 45:23.790
One time, I went to the
bathroom and I didn't wash my hands.

45:24.800 --> 45:28.110
One time, I used your
toothbrush to get dog poop off my shoe.

45:29.040 --> 45:30.109
Wait. What?

45:33.880 --> 45:35.711
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH SCREAMING)</font>

45:41.040 --> 45:43.076
Slow it down, slow it down, slow it down!

45:44.440 --> 45:45.429
Greg!

45:45.560 --> 45:46.549
Rowley!

45:47.280 --> 45:48.269
Greg, Greg!

45:49.520 --> 45:50.873
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

45:51.840 --> 45:53.831
Please! <font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

45:57.600 --> 45:59.158
Greg! Greg!

46:06.440 --> 46:07.998
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH PANTING)</font>

46:11.000 --> 46:13.434
You were supposed to meet us an hour ago.

46:13.560 --> 46:14.788
We were searching everywhere.

46:15.120 --> 46:16.519
<font color="#808080">MR. JEFFERSON:</font> We were
about to call the police.

46:17.400 --> 46:21.313
We're very disappointed in you, Rowley.
Very disappointed.

46:27.320 --> 46:29.038
They let us off easy!

46:30.480 --> 46:33.631
Why are you upset?
They didn't even yell at us.

46:33.880 --> 46:35.598
They almost yelled.

46:35.960 --> 46:38.952
That was nothing. My parents would
have screamed their heads off.

46:39.280 --> 46:40.679
They're disappointed in me.

46:40.920 --> 46:42.956
Big deal. Better than getting punished.

46:43.320 --> 46:46.471
Maybe for you. You're used to it.

46:57.200 --> 46:58.315
<font color="#D900D9">(YAWNS)</font>

46:58.960 --> 47:00.678
I can't wait to hit the hay.

47:00.920 --> 47:03.434
Hey, where are you going to sleep?

47:04.120 --> 47:07.430
I guess we're bunkmates!
Hope you don't snore.

47:13.240 --> 47:14.514
<font color="#D900D9">(SNORING)</font>

47:37.920 --> 47:39.797
I can't take this anymore.

48:16.800 --> 48:19.951
"Help. Get me out of here."

48:20.320 --> 48:22.834
"These people are driving me crazy."

48:29.760 --> 48:30.795
Send, send, send!

48:40.800 --> 48:42.677
Good morning, sleepyheads!

48:42.800 --> 48:44.518
<font color="#808080">BOTH:</font> Num, num, num, num!

48:44.640 --> 48:47.950
I have nine hundred and forty-nine e-mails?

48:50.400 --> 48:52.595
I need to go to the bathroom.

48:53.600 --> 48:55.477
I have to get out of here!

49:01.520 --> 49:04.034
<font color="#808080">AUTOMATED VOICE:</font>
<i>Your call cannot be completed as dialed.</i>

49:04.320 --> 49:06.993
<i>Please check the number and dial again.</i>

49:08.320 --> 49:09.639
What a piece of junk!

49:09.920 --> 49:12.912
<font color="#808080">FEMALE OPERATOR:</font> 911.
<i>What is the nature of your emergency?</i>

49:14.000 --> 49:15.228
Uh...

49:16.160 --> 49:18.037
<i>Hello? Are you hurt?</i>

49:26.080 --> 49:28.036
Do you have anything to tell us, Greg?

49:28.640 --> 49:30.198
<font color="#D900D9">(SIREN WAILING)</font>
- I don't think so.

49:30.480 --> 49:33.233
Anything about,
"These people are driving me crazy"?

49:33.920 --> 49:35.114
<font color="#D900D9">(KNOCK ON DOOR)</font>

49:39.760 --> 49:40.749
Yes, Officers?

49:40.880 --> 49:41.869
He has a knife!

49:44.400 --> 49:45.628
<font color="#808080">OFFICER:</font> Do not resist!

49:45.960 --> 49:46.949
Give me your hand!

49:47.360 --> 49:49.032
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>I tried to explain to Rowley's dad</i>

49:49.200 --> 49:50.838
<i>that I didn't mean to call 911...</i>

49:51.120 --> 49:54.112
<i>...but he really
wasn't interested in what I had to say.</i>

49:54.400 --> 49:57.233
You're always
getting into trouble with that Rowley kid.

49:57.920 --> 50:00.275
I'm starting to think he's a bad influence.

50:01.920 --> 50:02.955
<font color="#D900D9">(BARKS)</font>

50:06.800 --> 50:08.279
Hey, Rowley. How's it going?

50:08.800 --> 50:10.358
Okay, I guess.

50:10.880 --> 50:12.996
So, are we still on for the country club?

50:13.280 --> 50:15.953
Actually... I'm not going
to the country club today.

50:16.640 --> 50:17.709
Why not?

50:17.920 --> 50:20.912
What? Coming, Mom! Got to go!

50:22.680 --> 50:23.749
<font color="#D900D9">(RODRICK WHOOPING)</font>

50:24.800 --> 50:27.155
Ready to get my country club on!

50:28.880 --> 50:32.111
Rowley isn't going
and I can't get in without him.

50:32.480 --> 50:35.790
Okay. Well, you snuck me in.

50:36.160 --> 50:40.278
So instead,
sneak yourself in and then sneak me in.

50:40.560 --> 50:43.711
How? I need Rowley
to get me past the front desk.

50:44.000 --> 50:46.195
Greg! If you don't go to "work"...

50:46.560 --> 50:48.073
..."Dad"  will know you don't have a job.

50:50.200 --> 50:51.235
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

50:53.400 --> 50:54.594
<font color="#D900D9">(TIRES SCREECHING)</font>

50:55.840 --> 50:58.434
No problem, right?
Remember, you're a Jefferson.

50:58.720 --> 51:01.553
And don't forget to take out the trash.

51:03.360 --> 51:04.349
Hey.

51:06.560 --> 51:08.198
Aren't you going to say hello?

51:10.560 --> 51:11.629
Yes.

51:12.000 --> 51:14.355
How rude of me. Hello.

51:24.960 --> 51:26.029
Hey, Rowley!

51:27.320 --> 51:28.389
- Hey, Greg.
- Cool.

51:28.640 --> 51:30.153
I didn't expect to see you here.

51:30.400 --> 51:34.518
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font> Yeah!
Well, my plans changed.

51:35.200 --> 51:38.192
I changed my... change. I mean...

51:38.560 --> 51:40.551
Maybe I'll catch up with you later?

51:44.440 --> 51:45.668
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> I don't believe it!

51:46.400 --> 51:49.392
You lied. You never lie!

51:50.240 --> 51:53.073
My parents don't want me
to invite you anymore.

51:53.440 --> 51:56.238
I thought if I lied,
I wouldn't hurt your feelings.

52:10.040 --> 52:11.109
Ugh.

52:22.160 --> 52:23.798
That was impressive.

52:52.440 --> 52:53.998
That's pretty high.

52:54.240 --> 52:55.958
<font color="#808080">GIRL:</font> Are you talking to yourself?

52:59.000 --> 53:00.433
No. Of course not!

53:00.760 --> 53:03.433
You were. You're talking to
yourself because you're scared.

53:04.080 --> 53:05.069
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)</font>

53:05.560 --> 53:07.755
I'm not scared. That's crazy!

53:08.600 --> 53:11.637
You don't understand
because you're just a little kid.

53:13.720 --> 53:14.948
Then go.

53:47.960 --> 53:49.552
<font color="#808080">HEATHER:</font> Holly! Where's your sunblock?

53:53.400 --> 53:55.277
<font color="#D900D9">(DIVING BOARD SHAKING)</font>
- Whoa!

53:57.200 --> 53:58.428
<font color="#D900D9">(BATHING SUIT RIPPING)</font>

53:59.400 --> 54:00.515
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGHING)</font>

54:04.240 --> 54:05.355
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

54:13.240 --> 54:14.275
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font> Oh!

54:20.440 --> 54:22.795
I'm sorry. I don't understand.

54:23.160 --> 54:25.390
You see, I'm just a little kid.

54:29.880 --> 54:30.949
<font color="#808080">HOLLY:</font> Hi, Greg!

54:33.240 --> 54:34.229
Hey, Holly!

54:34.400 --> 54:37.551
Oh, my gosh, it is so hot out.
It's nice to cool off in here.

54:37.880 --> 54:39.279
Yeah, great.

54:39.640 --> 54:42.029
I was going to get ice cream.
Want to join me?

54:42.560 --> 54:43.913
That'd be awesome!

54:44.920 --> 54:46.797
I mean, no.

54:47.200 --> 54:48.394
Another time, maybe.

54:48.640 --> 54:50.358
You sure? It's really good here.

54:51.800 --> 54:55.759
Yeah. I'm trying to lose a couple pounds.
Thanks anyways.

54:56.920 --> 54:58.035
Okay.

55:13.120 --> 55:15.953
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i> I am not the kind of person who
likes skinny dipping...</i>

55:16.280 --> 55:20.068
<i>...but I had no choice but to splash around
all day, avoiding people.</i>

55:20.320 --> 55:22.788
<font color="#808080">MAN <font color="#D900D9">(ON PA)</font>:</font> <i>Attention, everybody,
the club will be closing in 10 minutes,</i>

55:22.920 --> 55:24.831
<i>so everyone out of the pool.</i>

55:29.240 --> 55:30.309
Rowley!

55:31.640 --> 55:33.676
Wait! I need help!

55:34.240 --> 55:35.753
How can I help you, sir?

55:36.440 --> 55:37.509
Oh...

55:40.280 --> 55:41.554
Could you pass me those?

55:42.680 --> 55:43.669
These?

55:45.920 --> 55:46.989
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)</font>

55:49.080 --> 55:50.593
<i><font color="#D900D9">(WALK LIKE A MAN</i> PLAYING)</font>

56:03.240 --> 56:04.468
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

56:04.600 --> 56:05.999
Oh, my gosh!

56:06.360 --> 56:07.918
You loser!

56:17.560 --> 56:19.596
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>I'm pretty sure
that was the first and</i>

56:19.760 --> 56:21.830
<i>last time I'll ever go on the high dive.</i>

56:23.000 --> 56:26.993
<i>Unfortunately, with all the
excitement, I forgot about Rodrick.</i>

56:32.120 --> 56:33.189
Rodrick?

56:35.040 --> 56:36.268
Rodrick!

56:39.640 --> 56:40.629
Rodrick!

56:41.080 --> 56:42.115
Ugh!

56:42.240 --> 56:43.958
Why are you hugging me when Mom

56:44.080 --> 56:45.399
isn't here to see it? Get off me!

56:45.520 --> 56:46.555
Where have you been?

56:47.400 --> 56:49.470
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Things might
be getting harder at the country club,</i>

56:49.720 --> 56:52.109
<i>but my fake job
made things much easier with Dad.</i>

56:52.440 --> 56:53.668
Oh, brother.

56:55.360 --> 56:58.955
Daddy, can you make my hiccups hic down?

56:59.200 --> 57:01.395
I have to pick up Manny from his play date.

57:01.560 --> 57:03.790
We'll have dinner when I get back.

57:10.200 --> 57:11.269
Dad?

57:13.560 --> 57:14.549
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> Oh, no.

57:16.000 --> 57:17.991
I'm already in enough trouble.

57:19.000 --> 57:21.070
If that dog does anything to Tingy...

57:21.400 --> 57:22.628
Slow.

57:23.960 --> 57:25.029
Go.

57:34.520 --> 57:36.750
Good Sweetie.

57:37.560 --> 57:39.915
Who's a good boy?

57:41.240 --> 57:44.073
Who's going to give Tingy to Daddy?

57:44.600 --> 57:46.158
You are.

57:47.360 --> 57:48.588
You are!

57:49.720 --> 57:51.438
Come on, come on!

57:51.840 --> 57:53.558
Go that way, go that way!

58:02.200 --> 58:03.428
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLING)</font>

58:11.520 --> 58:12.873
I have an idea.

58:17.400 --> 58:18.389
Here, Sweetie.

58:18.680 --> 58:20.875
Good idea. Good thinking!

58:24.160 --> 58:25.149
Oh, good.

58:25.280 --> 58:26.315
Come on, Sweetie.

58:26.520 --> 58:28.556
Good, good, good, good.

58:30.360 --> 58:31.349
Ha!

58:31.480 --> 58:32.708
I got it!

58:33.080 --> 58:34.308
Don't let him have that.

58:35.400 --> 58:36.435
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> Sweetie!

58:36.600 --> 58:38.716
Don't let him have that! Don't eat that!

58:44.360 --> 58:45.475
Oh.

58:57.560 --> 58:59.915
Is that... dog spit?

59:00.360 --> 59:03.033
How could there be so much?

59:04.840 --> 59:05.829
- Susan!
- Mom!

59:06.040 --> 59:09.271
You go clean the house.
I'll clean the roast! Go!

59:16.760 --> 59:18.876
You boys barely touched your pot roast.

59:19.640 --> 59:22.154
Are you kidding? I'm stuffed.

59:22.440 --> 59:24.317
I filled up on vegetables.

59:24.600 --> 59:26.158
<font color="#808080">RODRICK:</font> More for us, then.

59:28.120 --> 59:29.269
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMS)</font>

59:29.400 --> 59:32.153
I don't know what you did different...

59:32.440 --> 59:36.069
...but this pot roast is unbelievable.

59:38.360 --> 59:39.588
Chef's secret.

59:42.040 --> 59:43.109
<font color="#808080">RODRICK:</font> Great.

59:43.400 --> 59:44.628
And juicier!

59:57.560 --> 59:58.788
<font color="#808080">RECEPTIONIST:</font> And you are?

01:00:03.800 --> 01:00:05.358
I'm Roland Gropper.

01:00:05.720 --> 01:00:07.039
Have a nice day, Roland.

01:00:09.640 --> 01:00:11.198
Okay, you told one lie.

01:00:11.800 --> 01:00:14.872
I can accept that.
But this is getting out of control.

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:16.228
I think you have a lying problem.

01:00:16.520 --> 01:00:20.638
I didn't lie about coming to the club today!
We didn't even talk today.

01:00:21.240 --> 01:00:24.550
And how do you
keep getting in here without me?

01:00:24.920 --> 01:00:26.638
Wait. You're not a member?

01:00:26.920 --> 01:00:28.876
Anyone want a smoothie?

01:00:29.320 --> 01:00:32.471
I don't care whether you're a member...
but why sneak in?

01:00:34.920 --> 01:00:36.876
I wanted to hang out with you.

01:00:37.160 --> 01:00:39.754
I gave you my phone number.
Why not just call me?

01:00:40.040 --> 01:00:42.554
I tried, but I only had
half the number, and...

01:00:42.840 --> 01:00:45.354
I'm freaking out!
The D.J. for my Sweet Sixteen canceled...

01:00:45.640 --> 01:00:48.950
...so he can fly to Africa
to help build a hospital. What a jerk!

01:00:49.240 --> 01:00:51.515
Now what do I do for music? Whistle?

01:00:52.200 --> 01:00:53.189
What about live music?

01:00:54.600 --> 01:00:55.999
Do you know the band Löded Diper?

01:00:56.760 --> 01:00:57.988
Ew. That's a gross name.

01:00:58.280 --> 01:00:59.998
Live music would be really cool!

01:01:00.120 --> 01:01:02.873
You'd be the first at our
school to have a real band.

01:01:03.880 --> 01:01:04.949
That's true.

01:01:05.240 --> 01:01:08.152
They're just
coming off a world tour and are in town.

01:01:08.440 --> 01:01:10.715
I could get them to come as a favor for me.

01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:12.228
What kind of music do they play?

01:01:12.520 --> 01:01:14.795
Anything! They can play anything.

01:01:25.160 --> 01:01:26.149
Hey!

01:01:26.840 --> 01:01:27.829
Where were you?

01:01:28.040 --> 01:01:30.713
Rodrick, you are going to owe
me the rest of your life.

01:01:31.480 --> 01:01:34.153
I got Löded Diper a gig...

01:01:34.520 --> 01:01:37.114
...playing at Heather Hills' Sweet Sixteen.

01:01:38.360 --> 01:01:39.429
Really?

01:01:39.880 --> 01:01:40.915
<font color="#D900D9">(BREATHING HEAVILY)</font>

01:01:41.720 --> 01:01:43.039
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFLING)</font>

01:01:56.120 --> 01:01:57.997
Löded Diper activate.

01:02:00.120 --> 01:02:01.599
- You have her favorite song.
- Song, check.

01:02:01.880 --> 01:02:03.438
- She wants you in tuxes.
- Tuxes, check.

01:02:03.720 --> 01:02:05.108
You're ignoring
everything I'm saying, aren't you?

01:02:05.200 --> 01:02:06.269
Ignoring you, check.

01:02:06.520 --> 01:02:10.229
Don't worry, little bro.
It's going to be a good show. The best.

01:02:15.240 --> 01:02:19.028
Rowley! What are you doing next week?
Löded Diper needs roadies!

01:02:19.320 --> 01:02:21.356
How can you
stand to be near me when I lied?

01:02:21.960 --> 01:02:23.188
- What?
- I'm a liar.

01:02:23.480 --> 01:02:25.675
You can never trust me again.

01:02:25.800 --> 01:02:27.677
The sacred bond of our
friendship is broken.

01:02:27.960 --> 01:02:31.509
Rowley, I get it.
You didn't want to hurt my feelings.

01:02:32.760 --> 01:02:35.832
And I didn't mean to
get you in trouble with the Cranium Shaker.

01:02:36.280 --> 01:02:37.679
That's all right.

01:02:38.040 --> 01:02:41.999
It was actually pretty fun.
Now we can say we've really lived.

01:02:42.280 --> 01:02:44.635
So what about the gig?

01:02:44.920 --> 01:02:46.319
I've always wanted to be a roadie!

01:02:54.200 --> 01:02:55.918
Rise and shine, buddy!

01:02:56.600 --> 01:02:58.318
Don't want to be late for work.

01:02:58.600 --> 01:03:01.831
I'll drop you off at
the way to the office, okay?

01:03:02.600 --> 01:03:04.556
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>Now Holly knows I'm not a member,</i>

01:03:04.720 --> 01:03:06.711
<i>there's no reason
to sneak into the country club.</i>

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:08.956
<i>But if my dad finds out I don't really have</i>

01:03:09.120 --> 01:03:11.111
<i>a job, my life won't be worth living.</i>

01:03:11.480 --> 01:03:12.549
Thanks, Dad.

01:03:16.280 --> 01:03:19.556
<i>I'm even
considering telling him I got downsized.</i>

01:03:19.680 --> 01:03:20.749
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> Hey.

01:03:23.160 --> 01:03:24.878
<font color="#808080">GREG:</font> <i>But I don't think he'll like it.</i>

01:03:25.560 --> 01:03:27.278
<i>The thing is, I'm using...</i>

01:03:27.560 --> 01:03:30.711
<i>...so many identities,
I'm having trouble keeping track of them.</i>

01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:32.877
<font color="#808080">MR. JEFFERSON:</font>
This bill is five times the normal amount.

01:03:33.240 --> 01:03:34.468
I'm sorry, Mr. Jefferson,

01:03:34.640 --> 01:03:37.996
but your son has been
ordering a lot of smoothies this month.

01:03:38.360 --> 01:03:40.078
There he is now.

01:03:40.680 --> 01:03:41.908
That is not my son.

01:03:42.200 --> 01:03:43.758
Of course. That's Roland Gropper.

01:03:44.040 --> 01:03:45.268
Good morning, Arthur!

01:03:45.560 --> 01:03:46.788
Hey, Rowley!

01:03:47.160 --> 01:03:49.833
Rowley! My man! What's up?

01:03:52.120 --> 01:03:54.315
Hey! You forgot your sunblock.

01:03:55.800 --> 01:03:56.789
Frank Heffley.

01:03:58.040 --> 01:04:00.554
Your son racked up
a lot of charges on my account.

01:04:00.840 --> 01:04:03.035
What? He works here. Tell him.

01:04:03.320 --> 01:04:06.710
There must be some mistake.
We don't employ minors.

01:04:17.160 --> 01:04:18.479
<font color="#D900D9">(QUIETLY)</font> Do you not work here?

01:04:21.400 --> 01:04:22.799
Maybe not.

01:04:23.080 --> 01:04:24.115
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:04:43.640 --> 01:04:46.950
$260 worth of smoothies?
What were you thinking?

01:04:48.120 --> 01:04:50.634
I didn't know
you get charged for what you order.

01:04:55.320 --> 01:04:56.309
I'll pay.

01:04:56.600 --> 01:04:57.589
Very good, sir.

01:05:16.520 --> 01:05:20.229
Aren't you going to yell at me?
Aren't you mad?

01:05:22.680 --> 01:05:23.749
No.

01:05:25.720 --> 01:05:27.915
I'm just disappointed.

01:05:35.160 --> 01:05:36.388
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> We've got some serious trouble.

01:05:36.640 --> 01:05:38.517
Not you. Me.

01:05:38.840 --> 01:05:40.068
Yeah, mostly you.

01:05:40.440 --> 01:05:42.317
Look what I found in the mail.

01:05:49.560 --> 01:05:51.357
<font color="#808080">NARRATOR ON VIDEO:</font> <i>Welcome,
prospective parents,</i>

01:05:51.480 --> 01:05:53.550
<i>to Spag Union Preparatory School.</i>

01:05:53.920 --> 01:05:57.549
<i>Through these gates is a world in which
your boy will learn to thrive.</i>

01:05:57.880 --> 01:06:01.555
<i>Here we will impress upon him our
three cornerstones to success:</i>

01:06:01.880 --> 01:06:06.158
<i>Intensive study, physical exercise,
and, of course, discipline.</i>

01:06:06.840 --> 01:06:08.068
<font color="#808080">STUDENT 1:</font> <i>I used to play video games.</i>

01:06:08.920 --> 01:06:12.276
I was playing all the time...
sometimes two hours a day.

01:06:12.600 --> 01:06:15.751
I'd lie to my parents
and tell them I was studying when...

01:06:16.120 --> 01:06:19.317
...really, I'd sneak to the
mall to hang out with my friends.

01:06:19.640 --> 01:06:22.313
My parents sent me to Spag Union.

01:06:22.680 --> 01:06:24.432
My parents sent me to Spag Union.

01:06:24.800 --> 01:06:27.155
I don't waste my time
with video games anymore.

01:06:27.480 --> 01:06:29.277
Spag Union taught me there's more

01:06:29.440 --> 01:06:31.271
adventure to be found in a good book.

01:06:32.920 --> 01:06:34.069
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GASPING)</font>

01:06:34.240 --> 01:06:35.573
<font color="#808080">STUDENT 2:</font> <i>I don't lie
about where I am anymore.</i>

01:06:36.640 --> 01:06:38.232
Thanks to Spag Union

01:06:38.360 --> 01:06:41.397
and the tracking
device around my ankle, my parents know...

01:06:41.720 --> 01:06:43.278
<i>... where I am 24/7.</i>

01:06:43.520 --> 01:06:45.829
<font color="#808080">NARRATOR:</font> <i>Spag Union,
turning irresponsible</i>

01:06:46.000 --> 01:06:48.275
<i>little boys into men since 1925.</i>

01:06:48.600 --> 01:06:50.158
<font color="#808080">ALL:</font> Spag Union!

01:06:50.720 --> 01:06:52.233
They're going to send you there.

01:06:52.800 --> 01:06:54.358
I really messed up.

01:06:55.200 --> 01:06:56.235
What do I do?

01:06:57.120 --> 01:06:58.155
Wilderness weekend!

01:06:58.320 --> 01:07:01.517
You have 48 hours to
prove to Dad you don't need Spag Union.

01:07:02.080 --> 01:07:03.115
How?

01:07:03.960 --> 01:07:07.919
By being the all-time
best Wilderness Explorer there ever was.

01:07:11.160 --> 01:07:14.630
You can't go to Spag Union!
I don't want to go to school without you!

01:07:15.640 --> 01:07:17.517
It's not really my choice.

01:07:17.960 --> 01:07:22.954
Hello to the end
of the beginning of it all

01:07:23.560 --> 01:07:28.236
<i>Summer takes a fall
It's winner take it all</i>

01:07:29.040 --> 01:07:33.397
<i>And if you are not understood
I understand</i>

01:07:36.960 --> 01:07:41.954
<i>Goodbye to the days that
we filled with make believe</i>

01:07:42.600 --> 01:07:47.276
<i>As far as we could see
Possibility</i>

01:07:47.920 --> 01:07:52.072
<i>We dreamed of all the things
we thought we'd</i>

01:07:52.720 --> 01:07:55.598
<i>Never do.</i>

01:08:00.760 --> 01:08:03.274
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> You got it? Is it solid?

01:08:03.840 --> 01:08:04.829
Yes, sir!

01:08:06.720 --> 01:08:07.709
"Sir"?

01:08:16.279 --> 01:08:17.712
<font color="#808080">STAN:</font> What are you doing?

01:08:18.520 --> 01:08:20.238
This is where my troops set up!

01:08:20.479 --> 01:08:22.993
Come on, Stan. There's
plenty of good sites.

01:08:23.319 --> 01:08:25.993
Give me a break. You don't know the
first thing about camping.

01:08:26.359 --> 01:08:28.475
<font color="#808080">BARRETT:</font> You know the rules,
Stan. Whoever gets

01:08:28.640 --> 01:08:30.790
here first gets the pick of the campsites.

01:08:31.040 --> 01:08:34.350
The best way to
lay claim to a camp is to put tents on it.

01:08:35.399 --> 01:08:36.469
<font color="#D900D9">(BLOWS WHISTLE)</font>

01:08:36.600 --> 01:08:38.795
Explorers! Install camp!

01:08:39.319 --> 01:08:40.877
<font color="#808080">FRANK:</font> Hey, wait. Wait!

01:08:41.600 --> 01:08:44.113
Here, come on, come on, come on!

01:08:44.600 --> 01:08:45.669
Hold it up!

01:08:45.920 --> 01:08:46.908
- Put it on!
- I'm trying!

01:08:47.160 --> 01:08:48.559
Not here, over there!

01:08:54.040 --> 01:08:55.917
Move! Get the front!

01:08:57.399 --> 01:08:58.389
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

01:09:15.160 --> 01:09:18.357
<font color="#808080">STAN:</font> Sorry, Frank.
Doesn't look like there's any room...

01:09:18.680 --> 01:09:22.514
...for troops here,
but there's still plenty of good sites.

01:09:25.399 --> 01:09:29.996
Yeah, it's mighty convenient
being so close to the bathrooms.

01:09:39.840 --> 01:09:42.479
You all know the story
of the muddy hand, don't you?

01:09:43.800 --> 01:09:46.473
It was a dark and stormy
night, like this one.

01:09:46.840 --> 01:09:48.068
It is not stormy.

01:09:48.319 --> 01:09:51.915
In these very woods,
an old woodsman, a kindly soul...

01:09:52.160 --> 01:09:53.877
...was chopping wood in the rain for

01:09:54.040 --> 01:09:55.792
a group of Wilderness Explorers.

01:09:56.240 --> 01:09:57.229
So what happened?

01:09:57.360 --> 01:09:58.395
<font color="#808080">FREGLEY:</font> Nothing.

01:09:58.520 --> 01:09:59.953
If you consider the old woodsman

01:10:00.080 --> 01:10:02.196
chopping off his own hand was nothing!

01:10:02.880 --> 01:10:04.393
Didn't the Wilderness Explorers help him?

01:10:04.520 --> 01:10:05.509
<font color="#808080">FREGLEY:</font> No.

01:10:05.640 --> 01:10:07.517
They got scared and ran away.

01:10:07.680 --> 01:10:08.715
Why would they do that?

01:10:08.960 --> 01:10:11.155
Back at camp, the boys got to talking.

01:10:11.800 --> 01:10:14.553
They decided that
they should have helped the old woodsman

01:10:14.680 --> 01:10:16.238
because he was helping them.

01:10:16.600 --> 01:10:20.275
But when they got
back to his cottage, his body was gone!

01:10:20.640 --> 01:10:21.629
Gone?

01:10:21.760 --> 01:10:23.318
All that was left...

01:10:23.640 --> 01:10:25.198
...was his hand!

01:10:25.440 --> 01:10:27.112
I don't like this story.

01:10:27.480 --> 01:10:31.109
Not one of those boys was ever seen again.

01:10:31.480 --> 01:10:33.596
The only clue to what happened was

01:10:33.760 --> 01:10:35.910
a muddy handprint on the side of the tent.

01:10:36.760 --> 01:10:38.512
They say the muddy hand
is still out there...

01:10:39.480 --> 01:10:42.040
...looking for more Wilderness Explorers...

01:10:43.000 --> 01:10:43.989
...and...

01:10:44.400 --> 01:10:45.674
...revenge!

01:10:47.640 --> 01:10:48.868
I don't buy it.

01:10:49.400 --> 01:10:51.277
How can a hand move by itself?

01:10:51.480 --> 01:10:53.436
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING EVILLY)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(EXPLORERS SCREAMING)</font>

01:10:54.800 --> 01:10:55.789
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

01:10:56.160 --> 01:10:59.311
<font color="#808080">BARRETT:</font> I remember
